definitions.definition: A neurotransmitter in humans and other animals. It is an ester of acetic acid and choline with chemical formula CH 3 CO O CH 2 CH 2 N ( CH 3 ) 3 .

main_definition: ( biochemistry ) A neurotransmitter in humans and other animals. It is an ester of acetic acid and choline with chemical formula CH 3 CO O CH 2 CH 2 N ( CH 3 ) 3 .
